Implement Transition metatype variable binding in tap handlers

DESCRIPTION:
Transition metatype variables (e.g., `t` in `| Transition t |>`) are not accessible
in tap handler invocations. Generated code fails with "use of undeclared identifier 't'".

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
1. Transition variable 't' accessible in handler: `logger(msg: t.source)`
2. Test passes with output: "[TRANSITION] input:hello\n"
3. Transition provides: source, branch, destination

TEST DESIGN:
- Uses concrete source pattern (hello -> *) to isolate from wildcard issues
- Tests metatype that tracks event transitions (source -> destination)
- Simplest case with only one metatype variable access

ROOT CAUSE:
Same as 310_041 - metatype_binding transformation doesn't properly inject
variable scope into generated invocation context.

SOLUTION APPROACH:
See 310_041 - solution applies to all metatype binding (Profile, Transition, Audit)
